  "text": "In another study comparing virtual reality training to video training, Munz et al. randomized 24 novices to a either a control group, video training, or a training on the LapSim virtual reality simulator [CITATION_1] . The 16 participants assigned to one of the training groups each performed 30 min training sessions once per week under direct supervision. Analysis of pre and post-test scores showed significant improvement in both trained groups, but no significant difference in the improvement between the two groups [CITATION_2] .",
